d\theta / dt
 \frac{d}{dt}\tan \theta = \frac{d}{dt} \left(\frac{H}{D}\right) \Rightarrow \sec^2 \theta \frac{d\theta}{dt} = \frac{1}{D} \frac{dH}{dt} \Rightarrow  \frac{d\theta}{dt} = \frac{\cos^2 \theta}{D} \frac{dH}{dt} 
